{"session_id":"svc-1781516127126887734","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-06-15T09:35:27.205388274Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"opus-4.7","sticky":{"key_present":true,"bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"requested_harness":"claude-tui","resolved_harness":"claude-tui","harness_source":"request_harness","requested_model":"opus-4.7","resolved_model":"opus-4.7","reasoning":"medium","work_dir":"/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-9febbad2-20260615T093507-b49a1e79","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead in an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the contract: every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Too big if any holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across ~5+ files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, use a split-first pass.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, children once more; reject third-level splits with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child (copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add` only for legitimate child-to-child or sibling/replacement edges; never the parent.\u0026#xA;3. Use `parent=\u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` metadata and wire `parent -\u0026gt; child`.\u0026#xA;4. Write `no_changes_rationale.txt` under the bead metadata `bundle` path with child IDs, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Decomposition alone is success. Don\u0026#39;t mix it with implementation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC to concrete evidence (test, file, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Run git/index mutations sequentially; don\u0026#39;t parallelize `git add`, `git commit`, or staging/commit commands.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- If `lefthook run pre-commit` depends on staged files, rerun it after staging the exact commit set. A `no-staged-files` run is not acceptance evidence.\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; subject ends with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- Current-bead lifecycle is orchestrator-owned. Do not run `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --claim`, `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --status \u0026lt;status\u0026gt;`, `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --unclaim`, or `ddx bead close \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;`. Step 0 allows `ddx bead create`, `ddx bead dep add` for child-to-child or sibling/replacement edges, and `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;`.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `no_changes_rationale.txt` under the bead metadata `bundle` path before exiting. No commit or rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The `no_changes_rationale.txt` file under the bead metadata `bundle` path must contain one of:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` — repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` — open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` — operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` — blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` are rejected.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;For orchestrator decomposition, add `orchestrator_action: decompose` alongside `status: open`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Reports go under the bead metadata `bundle` path in `.ddx/executions/`. **Never write reports to `/tmp` or outside the repo**. Use a named in-repo path when given; otherwise write `\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md` there. Commit it with the code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other instruction files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Long-running matrix/benchmark beads\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;For expensive commands (benchmarks, load tests, validation \u0026gt; 60s per variant):\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Write a matrix plan before launching expensive commands: list required configs, output paths, completion criteria.\u0026#xA;- Do not re-run the same long-running command unless: (1) the command fingerprint changed (args/env/config), AND (2) you document why prior output is invalid and what changed.\u0026#xA;- If a long-running command times out or is incomplete, exit with `status: open` + retryable `reason` in `no_changes_rationale.txt`. Do not silently retry; let the orchestrator decide.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-9febbad2\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003eagent: enforce request-timeout as provider wall-clock cap\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;During dogfood of ddx-3b721804 on 2026-06-13, the worker was started with `ddx work --once --request-timeout 25m`, but the primary Claude provider process stayed alive for roughly 56 minutes while tool activity and watcher stalls continued. The operator expectation for `--request-timeout` is a bounded provider/attempt wall-clock cap with cleanup. DDx currently allowed the provider leg to run more than twice the configured timeout, which makes unattended burn-down unreliable.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\u0026#xA;cli/internal/agent/serviceconfig.go:24-33 documents `DefaultProviderRequestTimeout` and says `--request-timeout` applies to execute-bead/work one-off debugging.\u0026#xA;cli/internal/agent/agent_runner_service.go:112-125 resolves and forwards `ProviderTimeout` into the service request.\u0026#xA;cli/internal/agent/agent_runner_service.go:337-366 resets idle/tool-call timers on service events, but there is no absolute wall-clock timer that cancels a provider session that remains active through endless tool events.\u0026#xA;cli/internal/server/workers.go:734-787 forwards server worker request timeout into loop overrides, so server-managed workers will inherit the same ambiguity unless the boundary is made explicit and tested.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;Make `--request-timeout` an absolute provider-session wall-clock cap for execute-bead/work attempts, distinct from idle-read and per-tool-call timers. On expiry, cancel the provider context, reap the attempt process tree, release/park the lease according to existing timeout policy, and write durable evidence naming configured_timeout, elapsed, phase, provider PID, and cleanup result.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;Do not remove idle-read timeout or tool-call timeout. Do not call real providers in tests. Do not make long-running project tests impossible; if a longer cap is needed, the operator can set one explicitly.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. TestWorkRequestTimeoutCancelsActiveToolSession uses a fake service/provider that emits regular tool events past a 2s request timeout; DDx cancels at the absolute timeout instead of resetting the cap on activity.\u0026#xA;2. TestRequestTimeoutReapsProviderAndAttemptChildren proves the provider process and its attempt-scoped children are gone after timeout and process-cleanup evidence is written.\u0026#xA;3. TestRequestTimeoutEvidenceIncludesWallClockFields proves evidence includes configured_timeout, elapsed, phase, provider_pid, cleanup_result, and reason=request_timeout.\u0026#xA;4. TestServerManagedWorkerForwardsRequestTimeoutToAbsoluteCap proves the server worker path in cli/internal/server/workers.go honors the same cap.\u0026#xA;5. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/agent/... ./internal/server/... -run \u0026#39;TestWorkRequestTimeoutCancelsActiveToolSession|TestRequestTimeoutReapsProviderAndAttemptChildren|TestRequestTimeoutEvidenceIncludesWallClockFields|TestServerManagedWorkerForwardsRequestTimeoutToAbsoluteCap\u0026#39; passes.\\n6. lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:build, area:agent, area:work, kind:bug, kind:reliability, severity:critical, plan:server-managed-workers\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-9d1af129\" spec-id=\"IP-2026-06-13-server-managed-workers\" base-rev=\"f8dc38a4fa8998839fb9387a6abf536515d6218c\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260615T093507-b49a1e79\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cref id=\"IP-2026-06-13-server-managed-workers\" path=\"docs/helix/06-iterate/server-managed-workers-plan-2026-06-13.md\"\u003eImplementation Plan: Server-Managed Worker Supervision\u003c/ref\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"DDX_ATTEMPT_ID":"20260615T093507-b49a1e79","DDX_BEAD_ID":"ddx-9febbad2","DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","DDX_PINNED_PROVIDER_GUARD_LOG":"/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-9febbad2-20260615T093507-b49a1e79/.ddx/executions/20260615T093507-b49a1e79/embedded/provider-guard.jsonl","GIT_CONFIG_GLOBAL":"/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-9febbad2-20260615T093507-b49a1e79/.ddx/executions/20260615T093507-b49a1e79/embedded/git-global.cfg","GIT_CONFIG_SYSTEM":"/dev/null","PATH":"/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-9febbad2-20260615T093507-b49a1e79/.ddx/executions/20260615T093507-b49a1e79/embedded/provider-guard-bin:/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-9febbad2-20260615T093507-b49a1e79/.ddx/executions/20260615T093507-b49a1e79/embedded/git-bin:/home/erik/.local/bin:/home/erik/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/home/erik/.codex/tmp/arg0/codex-arg0Yu4YDA:/usr/local/cuda/bin:/home/erik/.jbang/bin:/home/erik/.opencode/bin:/Users/erik/.antigravity/antigravity/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/shims:/home/erik/.dotfiles/git-subrepo/lib:/Applications/SnowSQL.app/Contents/MacOS:/home/erik/.local/share/coursier/bin:/home/erik/.dotfiles/git-fuzzy/bin:/home/erik/go/bin:/home/erik/.dotfiles/scripts:/home/erik/.cargo/bin:/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:/sbin:/bin:/usr/games:/usr/l